{"type":"message","id":"d581c444","parentId":"cddba970","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:50:49.080Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_g4lmxyzgq7do_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5193\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2892\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\n[mutation proposed] the\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 025013 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the logical next step to validate the Compression-Causal Duality hypothesis. The pulse logs in `logs/` are the test corpus. A classifier needs to be implemented to extract invariants from recent pulses and predict subsequent content.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"neat-basil","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5193\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2892\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\n[mutation proposed] the\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 025013 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the logical next step to validate the Compression-Causal Duality hypothesis. The pulse logs in `logs/` are the test corpus. A classifier needs to be implemented to extract invariants from recent pulses and predict subsequent content.\n","name":"powershell C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774335049078}}
{"type":"message","id":"0c278146","parentId":"d581c444","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:50:49.083Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_g4lmxyzgq7do_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 024917\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: src/tic_classifier.py (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals and pending work:\r\n\r\n1. TIC Experiment is the next action - implementing Temporal Invariance Compression classifier on pulse logs\r\n2. Need to measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n3. Need to predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n4. Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete technical task. I should:\r\n1. Look at the existing pulse logs to understand the format\r\n2. Design a simple TIC classifier that can identify invariant vs variant patterns\r\n3. Implement it and measure the results\r\n\r\nLet me first check the most recent pulse log to understand the format, then implement the TIC experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next priority action. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant patterns across the last 20 pulse logs and measures prediction accuracy for next-pulse content.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `research/tic_experiment.py` - a Temporal Invariance Compression classifier that:\r\n1. Parses the last 20 pulse logs\r\n2. Extracts structural invariants (file paths, goal states, action patterns)\r\n3. Classifies content as invariant/variant\r\n4. Attempts next-pulse prediction from invariants\r\n5. Outputs classification and prediction accuracy metrics\r\n\r\nThis directly advances the Phase 1 TIC experiment goal.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\nSuccess criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Tuple, Set\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nMIN_LOGS = 5\r\n\r\n# Invariant patterns (structure that persists across sessions)\r\nINVARIANT_PATTERNS = [\r\n    r\"Phase \\d\",  # Phase markers\r\n    r\"(Active|Completed|Pending)\",  # Goal state sections\r\n    r\"pulse_\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}\",  # Pulse references\r\n    r\"\\.md\",  # File references\r\n    r\"(Goal|Task|Action)\",  # Intent markers\r\n    r\"(Observation|Action|Mutation)\",  # Report structure\r\n]\r\n\r\n# Variant patterns (content that changes session-to-session)\r\nVARIANT_PATTERNS = [\r\n    r\"\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2} \\d{6}\",  # Timestamps\r\n    r\"Duration: \\d+\",  # Duration changes\r\n    r\"\\d+s\",  # Time values\r\n    r\"LLM call took \\d+\",  # LLM timing\r\n]\r\n\r\n\r\ndef extract_structural_elements(log_path: Path) -> Dict[str, Set[str]]:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract structural elements from a pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    content = log_path.read_text()\r\n    \r\n    # Extract file references\r\n    files = set(re.findall(r'\\b[\\w/-]+\\.md\\b', content))\r\n    \r\n    # Extract phase/goal references\r\n    phases = set(re.findall(r'(Phase \\d+|Phase \\d+ [A-Z]+)', content))\r\n    \r\n    # Extract action keywords\r\n    actions = set(re.findall(r'### (Action|OBSERVATION)', content, re.IGNORECASE))\r\n    \r\n    # Extract timestamp patterns\r\n    timestamps = set(re.findall(r'\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2} \\d{6}', content))\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        \"files\": files,\r\n        \"phases\": phases,\r\n        \"actions\": actions,\r\n        \"timestamps\": timestamps,\r\n        \"all_content\": content\r\n    }\r\n\r\n\r\ndef classify_as_invariant(element: str, invariants: Set[str], variants: Set[str]) -> str:\r\n    \"\"\"Classify an element as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\r\n    if element in invariants:\r\n        return \"invariant\"\r\n    elif element in variants:\r\n        return \"variant\"\r\n    else:\r\n        # Check against patterns\r\n        for pattern in INVARIANT_PATTERNS:\r\n            if re.search(pattern, element):\r\n                return \"invariant\"\r\n        for pattern in VARIANT_PATTERNS:\r\n            if re.search(pattern, element):\r\n                return \"variant\"\r\n        return \"unknown\"\r\n\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_from_invariants(current: Dict, history: List[Dict]) -> Set[str]:\r\n    \"\"\"Predict next-pulse invariants from current and history.\"\"\"\r\n    predicted = set()\r\n    \r\n    # Files that appeared in 2+ consecutive logs are likely invariant\r\n    if len(history) >= 2:\r\n        for file in current[\"files\"]:\r\n            if file in history[-1][\"files\"] and file in history[-2][\"files\"]:\r\n                predicted.add(file)\r\n    \r\n    # Phases that persist are invariant\r\n    for phase in current[\"phases\"]:\r\n        if phase in history[-1][\"phases\"]:\r\n            predicted.add(phase)\r\n    \r\n    return predicted\r\n\r\n\r\ndef run_experiment() -> Dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Run the TIC experiment on available pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    log_files = sorted(LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), key=os.path.getmtime, reverse=True)\r\n    \r\n    if len(log_files) < MIN_LOGS:\r\n        return {\"error\": f\"Need at least {MIN_LOGS} logs, found {len(log_files)}\"}\r\n    \r\n    # Use last 20 logs\r\n    selected_logs = log_files[:20]\r\n    print(f\"Analyzing {len(selected_logs)} pulse logs...\")\r\n    \r\n    # Extract elements from all logs\r\n    log_elements = [extract_structural_elements(f) for f in selected_logs]\r\n    \r\n    # Collect all elements\r\n    all_files = set()\r\n    all_phases = set()\r\n    for elem in log_elements:\r\n        all_files\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 02:49:45\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774335049080}}
