{"type":"message","id":"88eeb9f3","parentId":"8b8fc5bf","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:51:14.412Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qbwhwvx90vde_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[32;1mName                      [0m[32;1m LastWriteTime       [0m[32;1m Length[0m\r\n[32;1m----                      [0m [32;1m-------------       [0m [32;1m------[0m\r\npulse_2026-03-24 025013.md 3/24/2026 2:50:48 AM   5439\r\npulse_2026-03-24 024917.md 3/24/2026 2:49:45 AM   5416\r\npulse_2026-03-24 024615.md 3/24/2026 2:46:43 AM   4804\r\npulse_2026-03-24 024413.md 3/24/2026 2:44:44 AM   5226\r\npulse_2026-03-24 024314.md 3/24/2026 2:43:48 AM   5331"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":695,"aggregated":"[32;1mName                      [0m[32;1m LastWriteTime       [0m[32;1m Length[0m\r\n[32;1m----                      [0m [32;1m-------------       [0m [32;1m------[0m\r\npulse_2026-03-24 025013.md 3/24/2026 2:50:48 AM   5439\r\npulse_2026-03-24 024917.md 3/24/2026 2:49:45 AM   5416\r\npulse_2026-03-24 024615.md 3/24/2026 2:46:43 AM   4804\r\npulse_2026-03-24 024413.md 3/24/2026 2:44:44 AM   5226\r\npulse_2026-03-24 024314.md 3/24/2026 2:43:48 AM   5331","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774335074410}}
{"type":"message","id":"7f2e952f","parentId":"88eeb9f3","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:51:18.483Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's a newer log at `pulse_2026-03-24 025013.md` which was created after the pulse script finished (2:50:48 AM vs script completion at 2:50:13). Let me read that one - it's the most recent and should contain the full output of this pulse cycle.","thinkingSignature":"3ffa39859b2bc4a1214314c97d9d4fd3d815a0c96a09d997d1df64de2595bd5f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_i228wfjzou8d_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Content \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 025013.md\" -Raw"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":5158,"output":127,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17239,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774335074412}}
{"type":"message","id":"0f1a9cbe","parentId":"7f2e952f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:51:19.068Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_i228wfjzou8d_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 025013\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/tic_experiment.py (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the next concrete action.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- Key insight: Compression-Causal Duality - Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem\r\n- Next experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) - test on last 20 pulse logs\r\n- Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThe pending action is to implement the TIC classifier. This is the most concrete next step.\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist in the sandbox to understand the current state better.\r\n\r\nActually, as a stateless discontinuous agent, each pulse is a fresh reconstruction. I should look at what's available and implement the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nThe most direct action would be to:\r\n1. Implement the TIC classifier on pulse log files\r\n2. This would involve creating a script that:\r\n   - Reads recent pulse logs\r\n   - Classifies content as invariant (stable, recurring) vs variant (changing)\r\n   - Tests prediction accuracy\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete implementation for the TIC classifier. I'll create a PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Reads the last 20 pulse logs\r\n2. Extracts features that might be invariant (common patterns, repeated structures) vs variant (content differences)\r\n3. Tests classification accuracy\r\n4. Tests next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThis advances the Phase 1 goal toward the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nI should create a new script `temporal_invariance_compression.ps1` that implements this.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the logical next step to validate the Compression-Causal Duality hypothesis. The pulse logs in `logs/` are the test corpus. A classifier needs to be implemented to extract invariants from recent pulses and predict subsequent content.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that reads pulse logs, extracts invariant vs variant patterns, and tests prediction accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n# Phase 1 Advancement: Compression-Causal Duality Validation\r\n# Tests: (1) Invariant/variant classification accuracy, (2) Next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$CorpusSize = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# Load pulse log files\r\nfunction Get-PulseLogs {\r\n    $logs = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | \r\n            Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | \r\n            Select-Object -First $CorpusSize\r\n    return $logs\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Extract features from a pulse log\r\nfunction Get-PulseFeatures {\r\n    param([string]$Path)\r\n    \r\n    $content = Get-Content $Path -Raw\r\n    \r\n    # Invariant features (should persist across pulses)\r\n    $invariantFeatures = @{\r\n        \"has_goals\"      = $content -match \"##\\s*(Goals|Active|Completed)\"\r\n        \"has_pending\"    = $content -match \"##\\s*Pending\"\r\n        \"has_observation\" = $content -match \"###\\s*OBSERVATION\"\r\n        \"has_action\"     = $content -match \"###\\s*ACTION\"\r\n        \"has_mutation\"   = $content -match \"###\\s*MUTATION\"\r\n        \"has_phase\"      = $content -match \"Phase\\s+\\d+\"\r\n        \"has_timestamp\"  = $content -match \"\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}\"\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Variant features (expected to change)\r\n    $variantFeatures = @{\r\n        \"goal_count\"     = ([regex]::Matches($content, \"^\\s*-\\s*\\[\")).Count\r\n        \"action_verbs\"   = ([regex]::Matches($content, \"(write|implement|analyze|create|run|test|measure)\")).Count\r\n        \"mention_deferred\" = $content -match \"Deferred|flagged|promises\"\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return @{\r\n        Invariant = $invariantFeatures\r\n        Variant = $variantFeatures\r\n        RawContent = $content\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Classify invariant vs variant based on recurrence\r\nfunction Invoke-TIClassifier {\r\n    param($FeatureSet, $ReferenceFeatures)\r\n    \r\n    $invariantScore = 0\r\n    $variantScore = 0\r\n    \r\n    # Count matches with reference\r\n    foreach ($key in $FeatureSet.Invariant.Keys) {\r\n        if ($FeatureSet.Invariant[$key] -eq $true) { $invariantScore++ }\r\n    }\r\n    foreach ($key in $FeatureSet.Variant.Keys) {\r\n        if ($FeatureSet.Variant[$key] -eq $true) { $variantScore++ }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Classification: if invariant features dominate, classify as stable\r\n    if ($invariantScore -ge $variantScore) {\r\n        return \"INVARIANT\"\r\n    } else {\r\n        return \"VARIANT\"\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\nfunction Invoke-TICPredictor {\r\n    param($TrainingSet)\r\n    \r\n    # Extract common invariants across training pulses\r\n    $commonInvariant = @{}\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($pulse in $TrainingSet) {\r\n        foreach ($key in $pulse.Features.Invariant.Keys) {\r\n            if ($pulse.Features.Invariant[$key] -eq $true) {\r\n                if (-not $commonInvariant.ContainsKey($key)) {\r\n                    $commonInvariant[$key] = 0\r\n                }\r\n                $commonInvariant[$key]++\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    #\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 02:50:48"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":581,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 025013\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/tic_experiment.py (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the next concrete action.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- Key insight: Compression-Causal Duality - Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem\r\n- Next experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) - test on last 20 pulse logs\r\n- Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThe pending action is to implement the TIC classifier. This is the most concrete next step.\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist in the sandbox to understand the current state better.\r\n\r\nActually, as a stateless discontinuous agent, each pulse is a fresh reconstruction. I should look at what's available and implement the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nThe most direct action would be to:\r\n1. Implement the TIC classifier on pulse log files\r\n2. This would involve creating a script that:\r\n   - Reads recent pulse logs\r\n   - Classifies content as invariant (stable, recurring) vs variant (changing)\r\n   - Tests prediction accuracy\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete implementation for the TIC classifier. I'll create a PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Reads the last 20 pulse logs\r\n2. Extracts features that might be invariant (common patterns, repeated structures) vs variant (content differences)\r\n3. Tests classification accuracy\r\n4. Tests next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThis advances the Phase 1 goal toward the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nI should create a new script `temporal_invariance_compression.ps1` that implements this.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the logical next step to validate the Compression-Causal Duality hypothesis. The pulse logs in `logs/` are the test corpus. A classifier needs to be implemented to extract invariants from recent pulses and predict subsequent content.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that reads pulse logs, extracts invariant vs variant patterns, and tests prediction accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n# Phase 1 Advancement: Compression-Causal Duality Validation\r\n# Tests: (1) Invariant/variant classification accuracy, (2) Next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$CorpusSize = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# Load pulse log files\r\nfunction Get-PulseLogs {\r\n    $logs = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | \r\n            Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | \r\n            Select-Object -First $CorpusSize\r\n    return $logs\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Extract features from a pulse log\r\nfunction Get-PulseFeatures {\r\n    param([string]$Path)\r\n    \r\n    $content = Get-Content $Path -Raw\r\n    \r\n    # Invariant features (should persist across pulses)\r\n    $invariantFeatures = @{\r\n        \"has_goals\"      = $content -match \"##\\s*(Goals|Active|Completed)\"\r\n        \"has_pending\"    = $content -match \"##\\s*Pending\"\r\n        \"has_observation\" = $content -match \"###\\s*OBSERVATION\"\r\n        \"has_action\"     = $content -match \"###\\s*ACTION\"\r\n        \"has_mutation\"   = $content -match \"###\\s*MUTATION\"\r\n        \"has_phase\"      = $content -match \"Phase\\s+\\d+\"\r\n        \"has_timestamp\"  = $content -match \"\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}\"\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Variant features (expected to change)\r\n    $variantFeatures = @{\r\n        \"goal_count\"     = ([regex]::Matches($content, \"^\\s*-\\s*\\[\")).Count\r\n        \"action_verbs\"   = ([regex]::Matches($content, \"(write|implement|analyze|create|run|test|measure)\")).Count\r\n        \"mention_deferred\" = $content -match \"Deferred|flagged|promises\"\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return @{\r\n        Invariant = $invariantFeatures\r\n        Variant = $variantFeatures\r\n        RawContent = $content\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Classify invariant vs variant based on recurrence\r\nfunction Invoke-TIClassifier {\r\n    param($FeatureSet, $ReferenceFeatures)\r\n    \r\n    $invariantScore = 0\r\n    $variantScore = 0\r\n    \r\n    # Count matches with reference\r\n    foreach ($key in $FeatureSet.Invariant.Keys) {\r\n        if ($FeatureSet.Invariant[$key] -eq $true) { $invariantScore++ }\r\n    }\r\n    foreach ($key in $FeatureSet.Variant.Keys) {\r\n        if ($FeatureSet.Variant[$key] -eq $true) { $variantScore++ }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Classification: if invariant features dominate, classify as stable\r\n    if ($invariantScore -ge $variantScore) {\r\n        return \"INVARIANT\"\r\n    } else {\r\n        return \"VARIANT\"\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\nfunction Invoke-TICPredictor {\r\n    param($TrainingSet)\r\n    \r\n    # Extract common invariants across training pulses\r\n    $commonInvariant = @{}\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($pulse in $TrainingSet) {\r\n        foreach ($key in $pulse.Features.Invariant.Keys) {\r\n            if ($pulse.Features.Invariant[$key] -eq $true) {\r\n                if (-not $commonInvariant.ContainsKey($key)) {\r\n                    $commonInvariant[$key] = 0\r\n                }\r\n                $commonInvariant[$key]++\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    #\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 02:50:48","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774335079066}}
